#STATIC BLOCK AND CONSTRUCTOR 
Constructors are used to initialize the objects. For every class there will be a default constructor. 
Whenever we cretae an object constructor will be called, then object will be created.
Constructor has class name and method properties.


public class q2 {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Demo d1 = new Demo();
        Demo d2 = new Demo();
    }
}
class Demo {
    static {
        System.out.println("Static Block");
    }
    Demo() {
        System.out.println("Constructor"); 
    }
   
}

Static block :- it will be created with a static tuple. It will be called automatically.No need to call with either object or class.
Static Method :- For static method, no need to call with object. u can directly call with class name and here static will act as instance or object.

#RECURSION 
public class Recursion {

   
    static int hcf(int a, int b) {
        
        if (b == 0) {
            return a;
        }
        else {
        
        return hcf(b, a % b);
    }
    }

    
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Recursion obj = new Recursion();
        int result = obj.hcf(18,12);
        System.out.println(result);
    }
}

# CONDITIONAL STATEMENTS
Types : if , else , else-if ladder, switch case
These statements are used to check the condition and to print the relevant block in constant time. 
Example :- if(a%2 == 0){
              return True;
            }
            else {
              return False;
            }


# CONTROL STATEMENTS 
Types : Entry control loop , Exit control loop

Entry control loop  :- FOR and WHILE 
Syntax FOR LOOP - for(start;end;difference)

Syntax WHILE LOOP - start;
                    while(end){
                        diff;
                    }
When we know the range we will use FOR loop and when we dont know the range, preferred to use WHILE loop.

class Person{
    int[] arr = {1,2,3,4,5};
    for(int i = 0;i<n;i++){
        return arr[i];
    }
}


